snippet.textDisplay:
I think this video portraits the impact of social media and Internet (in general) on self-imagery, our forms of understanding the world, the way we communicate with each other... And how addictive and dangerous it can be to just get carried away in smoke and mirrors.

And it does it with a mesmerizing, unsettling and yet beautiful aesthetic. Props to the band and everyone involved in this amazing project! 🙌

snippet.textDisplay:
This could represent us (everyone) who is wasting his or her time being in a virtual world where we just watch memes instead of being with real people... it could mean that memes became our only friends. Let's be honest, loneliness is a big thing nowadays because we fill it with these things... we distract ourselves from it cause it's just easier to look at our phones instead of being with someone! with a real person! We are substituting human connection with internet...
We became slaves of it without even noticing. And we became despaired for attention. Because we all wanna be that cool person who has 1 million followers and that has a "perfect life". And we don't even notice that we are being fooled... That none of it is real...
